         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 16 April 1883. ¶ T. R. Wilson Esqr, ¶ Undersecretary. ¶ Sir,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.04.16b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Z83/3733, unit 1418, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">16 April 1883.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">T. R. Wilson Esqr,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Undersecretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Noticing that the hon. the Chief Secretary has brought the item of £900 for the purchase of the Sonderian collection before the Committee of Supply, and that Parliament has voted this sum, and that it has now also been reported to the House, I have the honor to suggest, that these £900 be placed early at the disposal of the Agent General in London, so that the widow of Dr Sonder in Hamburg, whose adress is Neubert Street 5, may receive the £800 agreed on for the purchase of the collection and such additional sum as the 36 packing cases may have cost, and that through the Agent General arrangements may be made for the safe transmission of these valuable collections, for insurance, freight &amp;c, for which the rest of the money (£100) will suffice, after the probably inconsiderable expenditure for the packing-cases.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I avail myself of this opportunity, to express my best thanks to the Government, for the liberality evinced in securing these important collections, which for all times to come will give to our botanic Institution an additional prominence in this part of the world.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's request was approved<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(T. Wilson to M, 24 April 1883)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the same day<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a letter<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was sent<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to the Agent General<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(letter not found). On 15 June 1883, R. Murray Smith of 8 Victoria Chambers, Victoria Street, Westminster [London] wrote to the Chief Secretary, G. Berry, acknowledging the remittance of £900. Wilson referred the letter to M for his information on 26 July, and M returned it 'with thanks' the next day.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Gov. Botanist.</p>
         </div>
